 384:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** /** @defgroup PWREx_Exported_Functions_Group2 Wakeup Pins configuration functions
 385:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   * @brief     Wakeup Pins configuration functions
 386:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****   *
 387:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** @verbatim
 388:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 389:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****                      ##### Wakeup Pins configuration functions #####
 390:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****  ===============================================================================
 391:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
 392:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c **** 
 393:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     *** Wakeup Pins configuration ****
 394:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     ===================================
 395:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
 396:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       Wakeup pins allow the system to exit from Standby mode. The configuration
 397:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       of wakeup pins is done with the HAL_PWREx_EnableWakeUpPin(sPinParams)
 398:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       function with:
 399:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****        (+) sPinParams: structure to enable and configure a wakeup pin:
 400:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****         (++) WakeUpPin: Wakeup pin to be enabled.
 401:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****         (++) PinPolarity: Wakeup pin polarity (rising or falling edge).
 402:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****         (++) PinPull: Wakeup pin pull (no pull, pull-up or pull-down).
 403:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
 404:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       The wakeup pins are internally connected to the EXTI lines [60-63] to
 405:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       generate an interrupt if enabled.
 406:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****     [..]
 407:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       When a wakeup pin event is received the HAL_PWR_WAKEUP_PIN_IRQHandler is
 408:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       called and the appropriate flag is set in the PWR_WKUPSR register. Then in
 409:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       the HAL_PWR_WAKEUP_PIN_IRQHandler function the wakeup pin flag will be
 410:Drivers/STM32N6xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32n6xx_hal_pwr_ex.c ****       cleared and the appropriate user callback will be called. The user can add
